Adobe AI Toolkit: Automated Video Editor
This project is a distributed AI video automation system. It analyzes video/audio for silence, generates a screenplay via LLMs, and uses a local GPU-accelerated Image API to create visual assets for automated Adobe Premiere Pro workflows.

🏗 System Architecture
The toolkit is designed to run in a Client-Server model:

Backend: Python-based logic for signal processing and orchestration.

Intelligence: Groq Cloud API for high-speed transcription and keyword analysis.

Visual Factory: Local Stable Diffusion API (via Stability Matrix) on a high-end GPU.

Frontend: Adobe Premiere Pro (ExtendScript/JSX integration).

🚀 Gamer PC Deployment (Step-by-Step)
1. Prerequisites
Python 3.10+

Stability Matrix (with Stable Diffusion WebUI package)

FFmpeg (installed and added to System PATH)

2. Installation
PowerShell
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Omarsghr/Adobe-AI-Toolkit.git
cd Adobe-AI-Toolkit

# Setup Virtual Environment
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate

# Install Core Dependencies
pip install requests moviepy librosa groq-client python-dotenv
3. Local Image API Setup
Open Stability Matrix.

Go to Package Settings for Stable Diffusion WebUI.

Add the following launch arguments:
--api --listen --xformers --lowvram

Launch the engine and ensure it is running on http://127.0.0.1:7860.

4. Configuration
Create a .env file in the root directory:

Plaintext
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
LOCAL_IMAGE_API=http://127.0.0.1:7860/sdapi/v1/txt2img
📁 Project Structure
src/signal_analysis/: Detects silence and generates cut maps.

src/transcription/: Handles AI transcription via Groq.

src/ai_logic/: Generates image prompts and creative screenplay logic.

src/visualist/: Connects to the local GPU to render image assets.

main.py: The "Master Glue" that runs the entire pipeline.

🛠 Usage
Place your source video in the root folder.

Update the filename in main.py.

Execute the pipeline:

PowerShell
python main.py
Import the generated adobe_screenplay.json and assets/ai_images/ into Adobe Premiere Pro using the provided JSX scripts.

